          "scid": "thig2.5:1.0.3",
          "en": "5. Cittā"
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig2.5:1.0.4",
          "en": "“Though I be suffering and weak, and all My youthful spring be gone, yet have I climbed, Leaning upon my staff, the mountain crest."
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig2.5:1.0.5",
          "en": "Thrown from my shoulder hangs my cloak, o’erturned My little bowl. So ’gainst the rock I lean And prop this self of me, and break away The wildering gloom that long had closed me in.”"
        }
      ],
